http://myfreedomfoundation.com/blog/liberty-live/detail/can-individuals-between-18-and-20-purchase-and-own-handguns> 

O.C.G.A. § 16-11-132
Possession of a handgun by a person under the age of 18 years

Georgia law only covers possession of handguns by those 
"Under" the age of 18 with varying circumstances, as well as those 21+. That means a person 18-20 can legally "posses" a handgun.


O.C.G.A. § 16-11-101.1
Furnishing pistol or revolver to person under the age of 18 years

This law relates to the sale of handguns in Georgia through a private party (you and I) sale. Once again, it only refers to those "under" the age of 18. The rest of the laws that apply to the sale of handguns and handgun ammunition in Georgia are federal laws which only apply to an FFL or manufacturer. (http://www.nraila.org/gun-laws/articles/2004/citizen%60s-guide-to-federal-firearms-law.aspx> 

O.C.G.A. § 16-11-126
Having or carrying handguns, long guns, or other weapons; license requirement; exceptions for homes, motor vehicles, and other locations and conditions; penalties for violations

title: For Sale:  Who Are These Idiots (PART 2)
postcontent:
--Trying to sell a gun with out-of-focus pics or no photo at all.
(And everyone's all-time pisser, the UPSIDE DOWN photos.)
--Just because your AR-15 has optics and an after-market grip does not make it a "custom" rifle.
--Most of us know one Generation of Glock from another, but as a courtesy go ahead and provide that info.
--Most buyers need and want more than just "Winchester 30-30" in the description. Is it an XTR, Ranger, Commemorative? Year of manufacture?
--Why are you asking more for your gun that what I can buy a new one for?
--A Llama 45ACP is not worth $450 no matter what you think.
--Know your AR-15 chambers. Is it .223 Rem, 5.56 NATO, or .223 Wylde?
--A 1, 2, 5, 10, or 20 year old gun is not "new" whether it's been fired or not.
--Just because you built it does not make it worth more.
--Of course we've got pro- and anti-union users of this site, so I'm sure I'll ruffle some feathers with this next one. I'm going to peg on Colt...
Colt has a union represented by UAW (WFT?) and for about the past 35 years has done nothing but manufacture over-priced sub-standard firearms. (Do just a little research and learn how they screwed around and lost the M16A2 contract.) At one time the Rampant Colt truly deserved its premium price and prestige--but those days are long gone. If you want to dish out over a grand for a run of the mill 1911 that has the Colt name on it, go ahead, it's your money. If you want a REAL QUALITY 1911 that won't send you to the poor house, look into the Ruger SR1911CMD.

...and finally...Only an dumbass is going to trade away a gun for your junk stereo, dirt bike, laying hens, drum set or tattoo services.
